   The user asked to read prompt.md and complete a TDD exercise implementing the MHPCO Claim Office system. This is an automated experiment run (no human-in-the-loop approval needed). The system has two operations: quoting premiums for magical item insurance and processing damage claims. The implementation must follow strict TDD using specialized skills (/test-list, /red, /green, /refactor). When all tests pass, write `experiment-done.txt` with "DONE".

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - TypeScript + Vitest testing framework
   - TDD Red-Green-Refactor cycle with mandatory skill invocations
   - MHPCO insurance pricing: base premiums, component bundling (3-alike for 60G), cursed surcharge (+50%), enchantment surcharge (+30% for level>=5), loyalty discount (-20% for >=2 years), first insurance surcharge (+10%), multi-contract discount (-15%), 5G processing fee, ceiling rounding
   - Claims: 100G deductible per event, cap at 2x insurance sum, enchantment>=8 at 50% reimbursement, dragon material at 100%
   - Floating-point safe ceiling: `Math.ceil(parseFloat(amount.toFixed(2)))`
   - Insurance values: sword 1000G, amulet 600G, staff 800G, potion 400G, components 250G each
   - CLI must read JSON from stdin, write JSON to stdout, entry point at src/cli.ts

